comments: false
---

The Department of Civil, Chemical and Environmental Engineering,
University of Genoa (Italy), has different openings for PhD positions in
the field of fluid mechanics, coastal engineering and oceanography. The
research will be carried out on different topics related to ocean
science and engineering.

List of research subjects and possible supervisors can be found here
https://eur03.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fdottorato.dicca.unige.it%2Feng%2Femaces%2F&amp;data=04%7C01%7Cmet-jobs%40lists.reading.ac.uk%7Cbc8800d25d42491341e708d914b6840b%7C4ffa3bc4ecfc48c09080f5e43ff90e5f%7C0%7C0%7C637563596393863735%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C1000&amp;sdata=XDPDRKI75ZawLfbRjVosLhcXabdeolzRTW62%2FvtXjVQ%3D&amp;reserved=0 and
https://eur03.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fdottorato.dicca.unige.it%2Feng%2Ffluamb%2F&amp;data=04%7C01%7Cmet-jobs%40lists.reading.ac.uk%7Cbc8800d25d42491341e708d914b6840b%7C4ffa3bc4ecfc48c09080f5e43ff90e5f%7C0%7C0%7C637563596393863735%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C1000&amp;sdata=j2yacjf6EWjFNndzIZDpA0dLtzr%2BUeC%2FZvPQAnYGPMw%3D&amp;reserved=0). One grant is specifically
dedicated to the development of remote monitoring technologies aimed at
marine services. Candidates, in order be admitted to the selection, are
expected to contact a member of the scientific committee of the PhD
program
(https://eur03.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fdottorato.dicca.unige.it%2Feng%2Finfo%2Fstaff%2Fcomitatoemaces.html&amp;data=04%7C01%7Cmet-jobs%40lists.reading.ac.uk%7Cbc8800d25d42491341e708d914b6840b%7C4ffa3bc4ecfc48c09080f5e43ff90e5f%7C0%7C0%7C637563596393863735%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C1000&amp;sdata=4ESCawuOv%2F%2BWvR7gAGEEbz%2Fjz2BE5ykHthbNKyfBymY%3D&amp;reserved=0 or
https://eur03.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fdottorato.dicca.unige.it%2Feng%2Finfo%2Fstaff%2Fcomitatofluamb.html&amp;data=04%7C01%7Cmet-jobs%40lists.reading.ac.uk%7Cbc8800d25d42491341e708d914b6840b%7C4ffa3bc4ecfc48c09080f5e43ff90e5f%7C0%7C0%7C637563596393863735%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C1000&amp;sdata=Ofd0VhpGMkTzohU4X343g0CGRJCMtKIrQDeq7z32FKk%3D&amp;reserved=0), in
order to discuss a possible research project to be developed during the
PhD and to obtain a local support letter.

The official call can be found here
https://eur03.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Funige.it%2Fen%2Fusg%2Fen%2Fphd-programmes&amp;data=04%7C01%7Cmet-jobs%40lists.reading.ac.uk%7Cbc8800d25d42491341e708d914b6840b%7C4ffa3bc4ecfc48c09080f5e43ff90e5f%7C0%7C0%7C637563596393863735%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C1000&amp;sdata=jsjtdnt9AtIuag1uQXgZm%2BZEeQkM5%2BEKSswGqTUIYkI%3D&amp;reserved=0
Candidates should apply to the Course in Civil, Chemical and
Environmental Engng (Curriculum FLUID DYNAMICS AND ENVIRONMENTAL
ENGINEERING, page 17 of
https://eur03.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Funige.it%2Fsites%2Fcontenuti.unige.it%2Ffiles%2Fdocuments%2FANNEX_A_XXXVII%2520-%2520EN.pdf&amp;data=04%7C01%7Cmet-jobs%40lists.reading.ac.uk%7Cbc8800d25d42491341e708d914b6840b%7C4ffa3bc4ecfc48c09080f5e43ff90e5f%7C0%7C0%7C637563596393863735%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C1000&amp;sdata=ZJ9IPFHecApgbqmJAWbvJhzrLh6ROh%2FFYNPiGWpt570%3D&amp;reserved=0)
and to the Course in Marine Sciences and Technologies (Curriculum in
ENGINEERING FOR MARINE AND COASTAL ENVIRONMENTS, page 88 of
https://eur03.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Funige.it%2Fsites%2Fcontenuti.unige.it%2Ffiles%2Fdocuments%2FANNEX_A_XXXVII%2520-%2520EN.pdf&amp;data=04%7C01%7Cmet-jobs%40lists.reading.ac.uk%7Cbc8800d25d42491341e708d914b6840b%7C4ffa3bc4ecfc48c09080f5e43ff90e5f%7C0%7C0%7C637563596393863735%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C1000&amp;sdata=ZJ9IPFHecApgbqmJAWbvJhzrLh6ROh%2FFYNPiGWpt570%3D&amp;reserved=0).
Deadline to submit the applications is the 15th of June 2021 at 12.00
PM, CET.

The conditions of the scholarship will match the University of Genoa
Doctoral scholarship, which provides funding for 3 years, with a net
salary of 1100 €/month (social security included). Medical care is
assured by the national health care system.

Requirements:
- Experience in computer programming (numerical modeling, Matlab,
Python, Fortran, C/C++, netcdf and grib files handling)
- Successful candidates will preferentially hold MS Degree in Civil
Engineering, Coastal Engineering, Ocean Engineering, Physics,
Mathematics, Earth Science or a in closely related field
- Strong mathematics and physics background
- Very good knowledge of spoken and written English
- Ability to be a team player

Please feel free to contact me for further information (please start the
subject line of your message with “[PhD DICCA] Inquiry”).
